The paper discusses the performance of pivot-based indexing schemes for similarity search, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and database systems (DB). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses statistical learning techniques, which fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the asymptotic performance of the indexing schemes, which involves analyzing the growth rates of certain functions, a topic that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses a sequence of datasets modeled as samples from metric spaces, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
